  ('en', 'Abeilles du rucher', 'Which bee species is probably the best known in Europe ?', 'Apis mellifera', 'Apis cerana', 'Apis florea', 'Apis dorsata', '2', 'Semi-domestic, the genus name Apis is the Latin term for bee, and mellifera means that gives honey.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bee'),
  ('en', 'Abeilles du rucher', 'What is the average lifespan of a bee during the summer months ?', 'One month', 'Two months', 'Three months', 'Four months', '2', 'Feeding on the nectar of flowers, a bee can live up to ten months in winter and only one month in summer.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bee'),
  ('en', 'Abeilles du rucher', 'What expression denotes a species of bee living in a colony ?', 'Social bee', 'Parasitic bee', 'Lonely bee', 'Honey bee', '2', 'Other species are parasitic bees or cuckoo bees who practice cleptoparasitism.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bee'),
