  ('en', 'Abeilles du rucher', 'In which maternity of the hive develop the future bees ?', 'Couvain', 'Beaker', 'Dormitory', 'Levant', '3', 'It is generally located in the center of the hive and is surrounded by honeycombs and pollen (bee bread) to feed it.', ''),
  ('en', 'Abeilles du rucher', 'How do bees avoid creating a suffocating organism ?', 'Swarming', 'Remage', 'Pollination', 'Perching', '3', 'This phenomenon occurs when a part of the bees leaves the hive with a queen (the swarm) to form a new colony.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swarming (honey bee)'),
